This paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation for biomedical image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for unsupervised image translation is a key component of the proposed method, which is a popular technique in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of both unsupervised and semi-supervised learning, which are subfields of machine learning (cs.AI). The experiments involve multiple datasets and segmentation tasks, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) research.
